1
00:00:21,840 --> 00:00:23,260
♪Wandering alone♪

2
00:00:23,260 --> 00:00:25,540
♪Walking far by dusk-lit streets♪

3
00:00:25,540 --> 00:00:27,430
♪Your eyes are as cold as clouds♪

4
00:00:27,430 --> 00:00:28,970
♪Faintly coming into view♪

5
00:00:28,970 --> 00:00:30,360
♪The city lights♪

6
00:00:30,360 --> 00:00:32,630
♪Lit up that single moment♪

7
00:00:32,630 --> 00:00:36,140
♪I can't hide or stop missing you♪

8
00:00:36,140 --> 00:00:37,640
♪I can't forget those moments♪

9
00:00:37,640 --> 00:00:39,280
♪Losing you♪

10
00:00:39,610 --> 00:00:41,320
♪Like the seasons in my memory♪

11
00:00:41,320 --> 00:00:43,290
♪Without winter♪

12
00:00:43,290 --> 00:00:44,920
♪Walking down the long, dark street♪

13
00:00:44,920 --> 00:00:46,460
♪Snow will never fall again♪

14
00:00:46,460 --> 00:00:48,200
♪Our old story was torn♪

15
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:50,610
♪Into scattered pieces♪

16
00:00:50,610 --> 00:00:53,430
♪Replaying every single scene♪

17
00:00:53,430 --> 00:00:55,980
♪After you left♪

18
00:00:57,530 --> 00:01:00,510
♪As if our documentary♪

19
00:01:00,510 --> 00:01:03,120
♪Lost winter♪

20
00:01:04,770 --> 00:01:07,180
♪The breeze speaks of good times♪

21
00:01:07,180 --> 00:01:11,080
♪Pure white devotion♪

22
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:13,990
♪Send out a letter♪

23
00:01:14,300 --> 00:01:17,780
♪Carrying my longing♪

24
00:01:17,780 --> 00:01:20,980
=The Double Game=

25
00:01:21,020 --> 00:01:23,940
=Episode 7=

26
00:01:24,590 --> 00:01:25,710
I didn't mean to.

27
00:01:26,040 --> 00:01:27,120
I'd better head back first.

28
00:01:31,710 --> 00:01:33,640
You held and touched me,

29
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:35,120
and you want to leave?

30
00:01:38,430 --> 00:01:40,150
I was only trying to help you.

31
00:01:41,150 --> 00:01:41,990
Help me?

32
00:01:44,310 --> 00:01:45,280
Were you helping me

33
00:01:45,760 --> 00:01:47,000
look for this?

34
00:01:51,680 --> 00:01:52,590
How could that be?

35
00:01:53,040 --> 00:01:54,510
I don't even know what that is.

36
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:55,680
It looks pretty nice.

37
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:01,760
It's the key

38
00:02:02,230 --> 00:02:04,640
to my phone and laptop.

39
00:02:07,510 --> 00:02:08,350
Really?

40
00:02:08,560 --> 00:02:09,680
That's amazing.

41
00:02:10,176 --> 00:02:12,472
But what's the point of me opening
your phone and laptop?

42
00:02:12,483 --> 00:02:13,960
I can't read any of it.

43
00:02:14,150 --> 00:02:14,990
Yeah.

44
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:16,590
I don't think what you're doing

45
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:19,030
is what Lin Zhi'er would do.

46
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:20,840
I'm even wondering

47
00:02:21,590 --> 00:02:22,590
if you really are her.

48
00:02:24,030 --> 00:02:24,960
Of course, I am.

49
00:02:27,150 --> 00:02:28,910
So, when you were touching
and hugging me,

50
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:30,710
did you mistake me for Lu Tingyu?

51
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:33,840
How is that possible?

52
00:02:33,870 --> 00:02:35,080
What kind of joke is that?

53
00:02:37,190 --> 00:02:38,120
Actually, I don't mind

54
00:02:38,750 --> 00:02:39,960
if you see me as your husband.

55
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:44,310
You... Lu Tingxiao,

56
00:02:44,490 --> 00:02:45,330
if you keep this up,

57
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:46,870
I'll go all the way with you.

58
00:02:50,870 --> 00:02:52,030
What are you doing?

59
00:02:53,150 --> 00:02:54,560
Didn't you say you'd go all the way?

60
00:02:54,750 --> 00:02:55,590
Is that not enough?

61
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:56,450
I can do it again.

62
00:02:56,470 --> 00:02:57,340
No more, no more.

63
00:02:57,350 --> 00:02:58,200
No more.

64
00:03:23,840 --> 00:03:24,680
We're closed.

65
00:03:25,190 --> 00:03:26,030
Leave.

66
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:27,840
Fei Yifan.

67
00:03:28,150 --> 00:03:28,990
Long time no see.

68
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:31,150
Jin Chanchan,

69
00:03:31,310 --> 00:03:32,750
you ruined my pool hall.

70
00:03:33,430 --> 00:03:35,000
I was just looking for you.

71
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:36,346
We can settle that later.

72
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:37,870
I'm here today

73
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:40,400
to ask about the fundraising scheme.

74
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:43,190
What's that got to do with you?

75
00:03:44,280 --> 00:03:45,120
Wait.

76
00:03:45,710 --> 00:03:48,150
That woman acting shady that day

77
00:03:48,430 --> 00:03:49,360
was you after all.

78
00:03:51,590 --> 00:03:52,430
That's right.

79
00:03:52,910 --> 00:03:53,750
It was me.

80
00:03:54,470 --> 00:03:56,000
Let's put our issues aside first.

81
00:03:56,310 --> 00:03:58,150
Your priority now

82
00:03:58,310 --> 00:03:59,560
is to get back

83
00:03:59,710 --> 00:04:01,080
the money in the project, right?

84
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:02,430
If I can help you

85
00:04:02,710 --> 00:04:04,870
and all the investors
get the money back,

86
00:04:05,190 --> 00:04:06,360
will you work with me?

87
00:04:06,710 --> 00:04:07,550
You?

88
00:04:07,910 --> 00:04:08,870
What could you do?

89
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:11,280
Everyone knows Luzhou Group

90
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:13,150
bleeds people dry.

91
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:15,870
I'm Jin Chanchan.

92
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:18,630
I expose the dirt.

93
00:04:19,310 --> 00:04:20,680
You know

94
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:24,720
what I'm capable of.

95
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,000
Once this is over,

96
00:04:28,950 --> 00:04:31,000
I'll clear up the pool hall mix-up.

97
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:35,320
Okay.

98
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:37,326
I'll trust you one more time.

99
00:04:38,270 --> 00:04:39,360
Tell me everything

100
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:41,040
you know

101
00:04:41,510 --> 00:04:42,350
about Lianxin Island.

102
00:04:42,390 --> 00:04:43,630
Don't miss a single detail.

103
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:47,000
Lianxin Island

104
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:49,310
used to be a small island
near the mainland.

105
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:50,870
The fishermen

106
00:04:52,310 --> 00:04:53,190
fished for a living.

107
00:04:54,307 --> 00:04:55,656
Around the turn of the millennium,

108
00:04:55,720 --> 00:04:56,560
a man came

109
00:04:57,870 --> 00:04:58,983
and persuaded the villagers

110
00:04:59,830 --> 00:05:01,560
to raise funds by investing with land,

111
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:03,870
saying they'd all prosper together.

112
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:05,880
Was it Lu Jianchuan?

113
00:05:06,950 --> 00:05:07,790
No.

114
00:05:08,310 --> 00:05:09,830
It was Lin Youqiang of Linhai Group.

115
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:11,946
That guy had no money.

116
00:05:12,630 --> 00:05:13,720
He sold most of the shares

117
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:14,800
to Lu Jianchuan.

118
00:05:15,630 --> 00:05:16,630
Lu Jianchuan

119
00:05:16,870 --> 00:05:17,800
was very lucky.

120
00:05:18,130 --> 00:05:19,349
After taking over the property,

121
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:20,273
he'd never made a move.

122
00:05:20,750 --> 00:05:21,680
And this land

123
00:05:22,120 --> 00:05:23,750
kept going up every year.

124
00:05:24,950 --> 00:05:25,790
Later,

125
00:05:25,870 --> 00:05:27,190
he bought several nearby islets

126
00:05:27,310 --> 00:05:28,390
in one go

127
00:05:28,750 --> 00:05:29,630
and put them together.

128
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:31,320
So,

129
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:33,390
this was the old Lianxin Island resort.

130
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:38,950
A heart-shaped island.

131
00:05:39,560 --> 00:05:40,400
Pretty romantic.

132
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:46,310
Just a developer's gimmick.

133
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,600
Lianxin Island was spread out

134
00:05:48,950 --> 00:05:49,863
and irregularly shaped.

135
00:05:50,830 --> 00:05:52,000
It took land reclamation

136
00:05:52,510 --> 00:05:54,000
to make it into this heart shape.

137
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:56,870
That must've taken a lot of reclamation.

138
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:04,000
Something's indeed off.

139
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:07,000
He broke it into pieces.

140
00:06:07,390 --> 00:06:08,310
Broke it into pieces?

141
00:06:09,383 --> 00:06:10,356
Check the public notice.

142
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:12,680
Total reclamation tops 400 hectares.

143
00:06:12,950 --> 00:06:14,430
But Luzhou Group and Linhai Group

144
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:15,480
used cover names

145
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:17,600
to split it into 18 subprojects

146
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:19,430
under 27 hectares each.

147
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:21,160
Under 27 hectares?

148
00:06:21,430 --> 00:06:22,720
Is there a reason for that?

149
00:06:23,190 --> 00:06:25,390
Any reclamation project
under 27 hectares

150
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:26,800
only needs local approval.

151
00:06:27,750 --> 00:06:29,120
But anything over 27 hectares needs

152
00:06:29,510 --> 00:06:31,270
National Oceanic Administration review.

153
00:06:31,830 --> 00:06:32,989
The process is much stricter.

154
00:06:33,390 --> 00:06:34,680
For a project as big as this one,

155
00:06:35,830 --> 00:06:36,830
it'd never get through.

156
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,560
So, you're saying...

157
00:06:39,870 --> 00:06:42,040
Luzhou Group split the reclamation plan

158
00:06:42,443 --> 00:06:43,989
to dodge national approval on purpose.

159
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:45,700
That's a serious violation.

160
00:06:50,980 --> 00:06:54,140
(Love Is Timeless like Pearls.
Pearl Bay)

161
00:06:59,830 --> 00:07:00,670
Yan.

162
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:03,040
You're still up this late?

163
00:07:03,750 --> 00:07:05,000
Here, have some fruit.

164
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:08,480
Aunt Hui, you read my mind.

165
00:07:14,950 --> 00:07:16,240
Is this Lianxin Island?

166
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:19,640
Aunt Hui,

167
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:20,950
you know Lianxin Island?

168
00:07:22,630 --> 00:07:24,480
I'm actually from Lianxin Island.

169
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:28,270
Why didn't you mention it before?

170
00:07:28,720 --> 00:07:29,560
Then do you know

171
00:07:29,630 --> 00:07:31,240
about the Lianxin Island project?

172
00:07:32,070 --> 00:07:33,070
Do you know Lin Youqiang?

173
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:34,200
This one.

174
00:07:39,630 --> 00:07:40,470
I do.

175
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:42,720
I know all about it.

176
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:45,440
Back then,

177
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:47,040
Lin Youqiang came to the island,

178
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:49,070
dressed all polished,

179
00:07:49,870 --> 00:07:51,680
and fell
for the Village Chief's daughter,

180
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:52,950
saying he'd marry her.

181
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:55,310
Lin Youqiang told the Village Chief

182
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:57,313
they should team up on development.

183
00:07:57,950 --> 00:08:00,070
If the islanders put up their land,

184
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:01,870
they'd get houses for free

185
00:08:02,430 --> 00:08:03,630
and get paid to build them,

186
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:06,000
and later, there'd be dividends.

187
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:09,240
The Village Chief liked the idea,

188
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:10,840
and besides,

189
00:08:10,920 --> 00:08:12,830
Lin was about to be his son-in-law.

190
00:08:13,830 --> 00:08:14,750
So, he trusted Lin

191
00:08:15,830 --> 00:08:18,240
and got the islanders to sign.

192
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,560
But in fact, Lin Youqiang

193
00:08:22,190 --> 00:08:23,720
was a fraud.

194
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:25,120
He was a real lowlife.

195
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:27,480
He had no money for development.

196
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:29,070
Once he got the land,

197
00:08:29,630 --> 00:08:30,470
he turned around

198
00:08:31,430 --> 00:08:32,510
and sold most of the shares

199
00:08:32,630 --> 00:08:34,080
to another man.

200
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:36,280
Was it Lu Jianchuan?

201
00:08:37,670 --> 00:08:38,510
Right.

202
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:39,840
It's Lu Jianchuan.

203
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:41,280
I heard

204
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:43,390
he used to be a poor nobody,

205
00:08:43,670 --> 00:08:45,270
then married a rich girl,

206
00:08:45,550 --> 00:08:46,670
and became wealthy.

207
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:49,120
After Lu Jianchuan joined us,

208
00:08:49,510 --> 00:08:51,120
he kept making excuses

209
00:08:51,270 --> 00:08:52,240
to stall the project.

210
00:08:53,390 --> 00:08:54,390
Later, we found out

211
00:08:54,670 --> 00:08:56,080
he wanted higher land prices.

212
00:08:57,720 --> 00:08:59,030
What a shady businessman.

213
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:02,630
After Lin Youqiang got the land,

214
00:09:03,910 --> 00:09:04,910
he showed his true colors

215
00:09:05,510 --> 00:09:06,670
and broke up

216
00:09:08,153 --> 00:09:09,500
with the Village Chief's daughter.

217
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:12,030
Actually, he dumped her.

218
00:09:12,550 --> 00:09:14,840
The village land wasn't developed,

219
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:16,910
the islanders had nowhere to live,

220
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:20,360
and the land couldn't be used either.

221
00:09:21,390 --> 00:09:22,630
Everyone started making a scene.

222
00:09:23,630 --> 00:09:24,480
The Village Chief

223
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:26,550
went to ask him to end the contract.

224
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:29,493
Only then did he find out

225
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:31,630
he'd been tricked

226
00:09:32,510 --> 00:09:35,200
into signing a full 50-year deal.

227
00:09:37,790 --> 00:09:39,320
The land couldn't be recovered,

228
00:09:39,630 --> 00:09:40,750
and the money was gone.

229
00:09:41,910 --> 00:09:42,910
The Village Chief felt

230
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:46,240
he had let everyone down,

231
00:09:50,870 --> 00:09:52,120
so he took his own life.

232
00:10:01,630 --> 00:10:02,470
Aunt Hui,

233
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:04,360
were you close to the Village Chief?

234
00:10:05,270 --> 00:10:06,550
He once helped me a lot.

235
00:10:07,720 --> 00:10:09,000
When I saw all this,

236
00:10:10,150 --> 00:10:12,120
I just couldn't accept it.

237
00:10:14,150 --> 00:10:14,990
Why is it

238
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:17,240
that good people suffer so much

239
00:10:18,150 --> 00:10:19,960
while people

240
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:21,910
like Lu Jianchuan

241
00:10:22,510 --> 00:10:24,120
and Lin Youqiang

242
00:10:24,510 --> 00:10:26,630
are living better than ever

243
00:10:27,390 --> 00:10:29,150
with the land and money by deceit?

244
00:10:32,030 --> 00:10:33,440
They'll pay for this.

245
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:39,320
Have some fruit.

246
00:10:46,630 --> 00:10:48,000
(Lu Jianchuan and Lin Youqiang)

247
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:50,550
(are even worse than I imagined.)

248
00:10:51,630 --> 00:10:54,270
(I'll expose all their wrongdoing.)

249
00:10:57,140 --> 00:11:02,140
(Speak for the Voiceless,
Empower the Powerless)

250
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:17,410
♪This door♪

251
00:11:17,810 --> 00:11:22,560
♪Lets in the sky outside♪

252
00:11:23,040 --> 00:11:26,600
♪With a voice even lighter♪

253
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:29,410
♪Than how you just greeted me♪

254
00:11:29,860 --> 00:11:31,230
♪I know now♪

255
00:11:31,560 --> 00:11:36,440
♪What the chill in my body means♪

256
00:11:36,790 --> 00:11:39,660
♪The moment salt hits the wound♪

257
00:11:39,860 --> 00:11:43,280
♪My heart still beats so naively♪

258
00:11:43,450 --> 00:11:46,440
♪To complete♪

259
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:50,650
♪A joy that needs no brave pretense♪

260
00:11:50,790 --> 00:11:53,290
♪How cruel sincerity can be♪

261
00:11:53,430 --> 00:11:56,980
♪Like a door with no key♪

262
00:11:57,290 --> 00:11:59,610
♪Maybe you just passed by♪

263
00:11:59,610 --> 00:12:03,190
♪The tears in my eyes♪

264
00:12:03,900 --> 00:12:06,450
♪You looked like you had nothing to say♪

265
00:12:06,450 --> 00:12:08,190
♪Then got so good at being cold♪

266
00:12:08,190 --> 00:12:11,030
♪That's why a smile feels so precious♪

267
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:13,330
♪Maybe you just passed by♪

268
00:12:13,480 --> 00:12:17,810
♪The tears burned into my heart♪

269
00:12:18,190 --> 00:12:20,480
♪Let's say silence was just for show♪

270
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:25,150
♪Even if I've grown another year♪
